title: For Sale:  WWII Japanese Officers Wartime Gunto, signed
postcontent: This is a WWII Japanese Army Officers Wartime Sword, Type Gunto 1943, or better known as Type 3. It dates back to WWII when it was developed to improve on the Type 98 sword. This sword is a beautiful, heavy, very clean blade, in excellent condition, with a cutting edge that measures 27 inches. It displays a straight hamon and is very sharp. The tang has two holes for strengthening the grip of the sword. It is stamped in two places with Kanji characters to record the name of the sword smith which I believe is Minamoto; see pictures. The iron scabbard is in excellent condition and retains its original paint, without any dings or dents, and only a few light scratches from use. The sword and scabbard measure 39 inches overall. This sword was carried back from WWII by a U.S. Army veteran and has remained in his family. The handle had never been taken off until I removed for pictures to show the signatures. I will include the original bamboo retaining pin. 100% of the proceeds from this sale will be returned to the family of the veteran. Again, the blade is straight and free of nicks, pitting, rust, or evidence of sharpening. Very clean example for an item as old as it is and a great addition to any collection. Please ask any questions that you may have and I will answer to the best of my ability. I will send additional pictures on request. Good luck and thanks for looking.
